properties.Name: PremiumTaxTreatmentType
properties.Description:
The tax treatment of premiums associated with the Life Insurance Product:

- Taxable
- Non-taxable
- Deductible
- Non-deductible

Premiums are generally considered personal expenses and not deductible.    Exceptions include qualified charitable organizations and premiums paid for life insurance by an ex-spouse
as part of an alimony decree, which are deductible.
